          </para>
        </subprov>
      </prov.body>
    </prov>
    <prov id="DLM1599209" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
      <heading>Principal Act amended</heading>
      <prov.body>
        <subprov skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>This Act amends the <emphasis style="roman">Copyright</emphasis> Act <emphasis style="roman">1994</emphasis>.</text>
          </para>
        </subprov>
      </prov.body>
    </prov>
    <prov id="DLM1599210" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
      <heading>Purpose</heading>
      <prov.body>
        <subprov skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>The purpose of this Act is to amend the principal Act by removing the rule that a person who commissions a work is the first owner of any copyright in the work. </text>
          </para>
        </subprov>
      </prov.body>
    </prov>
    <prov id="DLM1599211" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
      <heading>New section 21 substituted</heading>
      <prov.body>
        <subprov skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>Section 21 is repealed and the following section substituted:</text>
            <amend quote="1">
              <prov id="DLM1599212" irdnumbering="no" quote="1" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">21</label>
                <heading>First ownership of copyright</heading>
                <prov.body>
                  <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">1</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>The person who is the author of a work is the first owner of any copyright in the work.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                  <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">2</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>However, where an employee makes, in the course of his or her employment, a literary, dramatic, musical, or artistic work, that person's employer is the first owner of any copyright in the work.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                  <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">3</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>Subsections (1) and (2) apply subject to any agreement to the contrary.</text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                  <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">4</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>Subsections (1) to (3) apply subject to sections 26 and 28. </text>
                    </para>
                  </subprov>
                </prov.body>
                <cf quote="1">1962 No 33 ss 9, 13(4), 14(4); Copyright, Designs and Patents Act 1988 s 11 (UK) </cf>
              </prov>
            </amend>
            <follow-text space-before="no">.</follow-text>
          </para>
        </subprov>
      </prov.body>
    </prov>
    <prov id="DLM1599213" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
      <heading>Transitional provision for works commissioned but not made</heading>
      <prov.body>
        <subprov skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
          <para>
            <text>This section applies if, before the commencement of this Act, a person commissioned, and paid or agreed to pay for, the taking of a photograph or the making of a computer program, painting, drawing, diagram, map, chart, plan, engraving, model, sculpture, film, or sound recording.</text>
          </para>
        </subprov>
        <subprov skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
          <para>
            <text>If this section applies, section 21 of the principal Act continues to apply to any work that is made in pursuance of that commission as if the amendment made by this Act had not been enacted.</text>
          </para>
        </subprov>
      </prov.body>
    </prov>
